            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Why would it not be recoverable for neovim as whole ? It is just a problematic server. I think neovim should tolerate improper behavior by lsp server and try to recover. That is , possibly to shutdown this specific server (not receive more input) . But certainly not to try to call a dead coroutine ( as it seems the case now). And alert about it every sec.\n\nNow, when extracting the `content-length` fails, nvim will show a simple message to user, and after PR #35743, it will also stop resuming the dead coroutine and close that lsp client. Maybe we can close this issue as well?\ncc @mfussenegger @justinmk BTW, sorry for doing cc, and if it isn't encouraged here, I won't do it again in the future. ❤️\n\n<img height=\"250\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e35f03a8-6371-4a95-9f37-4154679cd2c0\" />",
